_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1208, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajiks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5353840157446746e-43, \"text\": \"Tajiks\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajiks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajiks\"}, {\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.094089705727686e-14, \"text\": \"Central\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"an intelligence blind spot\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"deeper ties\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"more than a dozen people\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"knowledge\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"the drive\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They include current and former intelligence officials, police, diplomats and Central Asian migrants who have been contacted by authorities.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.184313812888792e-20, \"text\": \"Central Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Asia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"current and former intelligence officials\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1377}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"diplomats\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1462}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outreach, which has not been previously reported, comes in the wake two major attacks this year that authorities say were carried out by Tajik members of ISIS-K, a resurgent wing of Islamic State named after the historical region of Khorasan that included parts of Iran, Afghanistan and Central Asia.\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"score\": 0.9999702101312168, \"rank\": 2.9790737152580497e-05, \"text\": \"Tajik\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tajikistan\"}, {\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"score\": 0.9965712144984205, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ISIS-K\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State_\\u2013_Khorasan_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 1651, \"end\": 1664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.56142058518685e-26, \"text\": \"Islamic State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Khorasan_province\", \"score\": 0.9992689287170341, \"rank\": 0.0007316056665344134, \"text\": \"Khorasan\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Khorasan_province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Khorasan_province\"}, {\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999999979709173, \"rank\": 1.9513088602090776e-09, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 1740, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.459824210728184e-15, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The outreach\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake two major attacks\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1554}, {\"ngram\": \"authorities\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"the historical region\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"parts\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"Central Asia\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A double suicide bombing in Iran on Jan. 3 killed about 100 people at a memorial ceremony for slain Revolutionary Guards commander Qassem Soleimani, while the Moscow tragedy on March 22 saw gunmen open fire at concertgoers at Crocus City Hall, killing more than 130 people.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 2044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999999979709173, \"rank\": 1.9513088602090776e-09, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qasem_Soleimani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qassem Soleimani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qasem_Soleimani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qasem_Soleimani\"}, {\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.628454897357066e-19, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A double suicide bombing\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1795}, {\"ngram\": \"Jan.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1811}, {\